00:01:04.030 --> 00:01:06.850
So, last day we looked at the
validation of the Bohr model.

00:01:06.850 --> 00:01:10.190
And we had two pieces
of experimental data.

00:01:10.190 --> 00:01:13.540
First were the hydrogen
spectrum lines,

00:01:13.540 --> 00:01:17.760
measured in 1853 by Angstrom
and fit to an equation by J.J.

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:20.000
Balmer in 1885.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:22.800
And, secondly, we saw the
Franck-Hertz experiment,

00:01:22.800 --> 00:01:26.910
in which we were able to
get the sense that energy

00:01:26.910 --> 00:01:30.000
levels within a multi-electron
atom, like, mercury,

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:32.020
those energy levels
are also quantized,

00:01:32.020 --> 00:01:34.240
which gave credence to
the quantum condition.

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:38.700
Which said that the movement
of an electron, the movement

00:01:38.700 --> 00:01:41.340
of an electron, is quantized.

00:01:41.340 --> 00:01:45.210
And then we started looking
at the limitations of the Bohr

00:01:45.210 --> 00:01:47.350
model, problems
with the Bohr model.

00:01:47.350 --> 00:01:50.370
And I said, in two
words, fine structure.

00:01:50.370 --> 00:01:52.230
And we started looking
at fine structure.

00:01:52.230 --> 00:01:56.340
We see that the 656
nanometer line in hydrogen,

00:01:56.340 --> 00:01:58.040
in point of fact, is a doublet.

00:01:58.040 --> 00:02:01.300
It's actually two lines
very closely spaced.

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:05.050
Bohr model is incapable
of explaining this.

00:02:05.050 --> 00:02:07.810
Zeeman looked at
gas discharge tube,

00:02:07.810 --> 00:02:11.470
measured hydrogen spectrum
in a magnetic field,

00:02:11.470 --> 00:02:13.280
and found line
splitting proportional

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:14.940
to the intensity of the field.

00:02:14.940 --> 00:02:18.090
Stark did similar experiments
only in an electric field,

00:02:18.090 --> 00:02:21.300
and also found line
splitting, the degree of which

00:02:21.300 --> 00:02:24.345
was proportional to the
intensity of the field.

00:02:24.345 --> 00:02:27.390
And the Bohr model is
incapable of explaining this.

00:02:27.390 --> 00:02:31.150
Sommerfeld, in 1916, put
a patch on the Bohr model

00:02:31.150 --> 00:02:33.790
and proposed that
the electron moves

00:02:33.790 --> 00:02:38.820
not only in a circular orbit
but also in elliptical orbits.

00:02:38.820 --> 00:02:40.860
And there's a plurality
of these orbits.

00:02:40.860 --> 00:02:46.565
But overall, the distance from
the nucleus to the electron

00:02:46.565 --> 00:02:51.320
orbits is more or less given by
the principal quantum number n,

00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:54.725
and the degree of
eccentricity is tiny.

00:02:54.725 --> 00:02:58.110
But, more or less,
described by n.

00:02:58.110 --> 00:03:01.360
And then to further
depict what's going on,

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:03.800
he introduced the
orbital quantum number

00:03:03.800 --> 00:03:06.900
or, as your book calls it,
the azimuthal quantum number.

00:03:06.900 --> 00:03:09.310
And the magnetic quantum number.

00:03:09.310 --> 00:03:11.420
And further said that the
energy of the electron

00:03:11.420 --> 00:03:15.410
is given by the specifications
according to all three quantum

00:03:15.410 --> 00:03:16.310
numbers.

00:03:16.310 --> 00:03:19.410
And then, lastly, in
order to get completeness,

00:03:19.410 --> 00:03:22.100
we jumped ahead in
time to 1922 with

00:03:22.100 --> 00:03:25.870
the Stern-Gerlach experiment,
which was the beam of silver.

00:03:25.870 --> 00:03:30.110
Atoms through a divergent
magnetic field, the beam

00:03:30.110 --> 00:03:35.070
split in two symmetrically
about the point

00:03:35.070 --> 00:03:39.850
at which the beam would land
on the slide in the absence

00:03:39.850 --> 00:03:40.980
of a magnetic field.

00:03:40.980 --> 00:03:43.080
And that can led to
some deeper thinking

00:03:43.080 --> 00:03:47.700
by two graduate students in
Leiden, Goudsmit and Uhlenbeck,

00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:50.340
who proposed the notion
of electron spin.

00:03:50.340 --> 00:03:52.980
And from that came the
fourth quantum number,

00:03:52.980 --> 00:03:54.900
s, and we're going to
throw that into the mix

00:03:54.900 --> 00:03:58.100
even though Sommerfeld didn't
give it to us back in 1916.

00:03:58.100 --> 00:04:00.260
But I just want to move
forward with all of them.

00:04:00.260 --> 00:04:02.980
And we recognize
that s could take

00:04:02.980 --> 00:04:07.660
on two values,
plus or minus 1/2,

00:04:07.660 --> 00:04:11.920
or we could call it
spin up or spin down.

00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:14.160
And, as you're going
to learn in 802,

00:04:14.160 --> 00:04:17.180
the convention in
electromagnetism

00:04:17.180 --> 00:04:18.490
is the right-hand rule.

00:04:18.490 --> 00:04:21.750
That is to say, the thumb
indicates the vector

00:04:21.750 --> 00:04:25.570
and the curl of the fingers
indicate the rotation.

00:04:25.570 --> 00:04:28.040
So we would argue that
this is an electron

00:04:28.040 --> 00:04:31.790
spin from looking top-down
anticlockwise and then

00:04:31.790 --> 00:04:33.130
vice versa.

00:04:33.130 --> 00:04:35.960
So that's as far as we got.

00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:38.410
And so now what
I'd like to do is

00:04:38.410 --> 00:04:41.520
to take a look at
the periodic table

00:04:41.520 --> 00:04:43.950
and get a sense of
electron filling.

00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:48.310
And whether that explains the
trends in the periodic table.

00:04:48.310 --> 00:04:51.600
And for that I'm going to go
to table 6-3 in your reading.

00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:53.710
And all we're going
to do, basically,

00:04:53.710 --> 00:04:57.960
is say, well can we can we
use this idea of n, l and m,

00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:01.600
and explain the order of
filling in a periodic table.

00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:05.530
So when n equals 1,
l must be equal to 0.

00:05:05.530 --> 00:05:08.150
And the m must be equal to 0.

00:05:08.150 --> 00:05:10.350
So that means there's
only one orbital.

00:05:10.350 --> 00:05:13.800
And, in that orbital, we
can have two electrons.

00:05:13.800 --> 00:05:19.760
So we've got the possibility of
two different electrons going

00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:22.100
into the 1s orbital.

00:05:22.100 --> 00:05:23.830
Then we go, n equals 2.

00:05:23.830 --> 00:05:25.610
l can take a value of 0.

00:05:25.610 --> 00:05:29.080
Which is the same as
what we had before.

00:05:29.080 --> 00:05:32.550
Just one orbital
in that subshell.

00:05:32.550 --> 00:05:36.750
Or we can have l equals
1, in which case m can

00:05:36.750 --> 00:05:40.660
take three different values;
minus 1, 0, and plus 1.

00:05:40.660 --> 00:05:42.400
So there's three orbitals there.

00:05:42.400 --> 00:05:44.070
3 plus 1 is 4.

00:05:44.070 --> 00:05:45.910
And that gives us
the possibility

00:05:45.910 --> 00:05:47.680
of putting 8 electrons in.

00:05:47.680 --> 00:05:49.110
Because this is n, l, and m.

00:05:49.110 --> 00:05:53.230
And then we've got the choice
of s plus or minus 1/2.

00:05:53.230 --> 00:05:54.180
And we'll do one more.

00:05:54.180 --> 00:05:55.420
We'll go to n equals 3.

00:05:55.420 --> 00:05:59.430
So at l equals 0,
we just have 1.

00:05:59.430 --> 00:06:01.500
When l equals 1, we
have the same thing

00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:03.770
as we had with the 2p.

00:06:03.770 --> 00:06:07.690
And then when l equals 2, we
have what's known as the 3d.

00:06:07.690 --> 00:06:09.710
Remember the
spectroscopists there.

00:06:09.710 --> 00:06:11.200
They don't like numbers.

00:06:11.200 --> 00:06:14.330
So they use s, p, d, f.

00:06:14.330 --> 00:06:15.030
But we're smart.

00:06:15.030 --> 00:06:16.680
We can go 0, 1, 2.

00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:17.700
It didn't hurt us.

00:06:17.700 --> 00:06:20.770
And we go minus 2,
minus 1, 0, 1, 2.

00:06:20.770 --> 00:06:21.610
So there's 5.

00:06:21.610 --> 00:06:24.080
So 5 plus 3 is 8, and 9.

00:06:24.080 --> 00:06:25.880
9 times 2 is 18.

00:06:25.880 --> 00:06:27.320
Now let's go to
the periodic table

00:06:27.320 --> 00:06:29.030
and see if this reconciles.

00:06:29.030 --> 00:06:33.830
So, when we have 1s,
there's hydrogen, helium.

00:06:33.830 --> 00:06:37.390
And then the next is n equals 2.

00:06:37.390 --> 00:06:39.740
So that should give
us 4 times 2 is 8.

00:06:39.740 --> 00:06:44.140
So, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10.

00:06:44.140 --> 00:06:46.940
So there's the 8 different
electrons that get us

00:06:46.940 --> 00:06:49.000
all the way over to neon.

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:50.760
And now let's go to n equals 3.

00:06:50.760 --> 00:06:54.750
So, I have 1, 2,
3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

00:06:54.750 --> 00:06:56.300
And then I'm over to 4.

00:06:56.300 --> 00:06:57.350
4s.

00:06:57.350 --> 00:07:02.450
But look, this is
saying I should have 18.

00:07:02.450 --> 00:07:06.610
18 electrons in n equals 3.

00:07:06.610 --> 00:07:11.670
So what I'm pointing out here
is that there's a disconnect,

00:07:11.670 --> 00:07:15.440
there's a disconnect between
the populating of electrons

00:07:15.440 --> 00:07:17.790
just in ascending
quantum number,

00:07:17.790 --> 00:07:20.570
and the way the elements are
arranged in the periodic table.

00:07:20.570 --> 00:07:23.120
There's some other
factor at work here.

00:07:23.120 --> 00:07:26.810
So we want to take a look at
what that could possibly be.

00:07:26.810 --> 00:07:39.360
And, so what we need is to
go to a modified energy level

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:40.360
diagram.

00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:44.560
A modified energy
level diagram, that

00:07:44.560 --> 00:07:49.880
can explain what the
filling sequence is

00:07:49.880 --> 00:07:52.300
in the periodic table.

00:07:52.300 --> 00:07:55.020
And the modified
energy level diagram

00:07:55.020 --> 00:07:59.156
is drawn on the basis
of the Aufbau principle.

00:07:59.156 --> 00:08:00.030
The Aufbau principle.

00:08:00.030 --> 00:08:03.560
Aufbau, German,
meaning construction.

00:08:03.560 --> 00:08:06.130
I think it actually
means out-build.

00:08:06.130 --> 00:08:10.720
But, anyways, it generates
the filling sequence.

00:08:10.720 --> 00:08:14.540
So, there are three parts
to the Aufbau principle.

00:08:14.540 --> 00:08:17.370
And the Aufbau principle
is going to govern,

00:08:17.370 --> 00:08:25.770
it's going to govern or direct
the electron filling sequence.

00:08:29.980 --> 00:08:31.890
Directs the electron
filling sequence.

00:08:31.890 --> 00:08:34.870
So, the first component
of the Aufbau principle

00:08:34.870 --> 00:08:37.910
is the Pauli
exclusion principle.

00:08:37.910 --> 00:08:43.770
Pauli exclusion principle.

00:08:43.770 --> 00:08:47.270
Wolfgang Pauli was an Austrian.

00:08:47.270 --> 00:08:51.720
He did his Ph.D under
Sommerfeld in Munich,

00:08:51.720 --> 00:08:54.130
and then he post-docced
with Born in Gottingen

00:08:54.130 --> 00:08:58.690
and on to Niels Bohr Copenhagen.
These people worked together.

00:08:58.690 --> 00:09:01.140
They traveled from
lab to lab, and it

00:09:01.140 --> 00:09:03.660
was a very vibrant
conversation going on.

00:09:03.660 --> 00:09:06.930
Eventually, he became a
professor physics in Hamburg.

00:09:06.930 --> 00:09:10.500
And the Pauli exclusion
principle, simply stated,

00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:15.380
is that in any electron
system, each electron

00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:19.650
has a unique set of
four quantum numbers.

00:09:19.650 --> 00:09:23.390
A unique set of four
quantum numbers.

00:09:23.390 --> 00:09:35.870
Any atom set, four
quantum numbers

00:09:35.870 --> 00:09:37.370
are unique for each electron.

00:09:44.492 --> 00:09:47.220
For each electron.

00:09:47.220 --> 00:09:53.530
So you can think of this
as the set of n, l, m and s

00:09:53.530 --> 00:09:55.300
as sort of the social
security number,

00:09:55.300 --> 00:10:00.730
if you like, for each of
the electrons in the set.

00:10:00.730 --> 00:10:04.439
And he eventually gets the
Nobel Prize for this, in 1945.

00:10:04.439 --> 00:10:05.980
Virtually everybody
I'm going to talk

00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:08.480
about today, with the
exception of Sommerfeld,

00:10:08.480 --> 00:10:09.790
gets the Nobel Prize.

00:10:09.790 --> 00:10:12.790
Sommerfeld is a very
interesting character, though.

00:10:12.790 --> 00:10:17.050
While he himself never won
the Nobel Prize, many, many

00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:21.350
of his students and proteges
won Nobel Prizes, to which you

00:10:21.350 --> 00:10:23.850
must include that there
was something very, very

00:10:23.850 --> 00:10:26.710
special about the quality of
the mentoring that he gave,

00:10:26.710 --> 00:10:30.070
that so many of his proteges
went on to win the Nobel Prize.

00:10:30.070 --> 00:10:32.670
So this is the first part
of the Aufbau principle.

00:10:32.670 --> 00:10:35.750
The second part is
that the electrons fill

00:10:35.750 --> 00:10:37.830
from lowest to highest energy.

00:10:37.830 --> 00:10:43.820
So electrons fill orbitals.

00:10:43.820 --> 00:10:46.280
You can think of the
orbitals as placeholders.

00:10:46.280 --> 00:10:47.820
They're really energy concepts.

00:10:47.820 --> 00:10:53.710
But we populate orbitals from
lowest to highest energy.

00:10:53.710 --> 00:11:00.345
From lowest to highest energy.

00:11:00.345 --> 00:11:02.220
Or if I wanted to be a
wise guy, I would say,

00:11:02.220 --> 00:11:04.540
I'm going to define
energy in such a way

00:11:04.540 --> 00:11:06.855
as I get that as the
filling sequence.

00:11:09.700 --> 00:11:11.880
One's got to fit the other.

00:11:11.880 --> 00:11:15.210
And the energy is
itself a function

00:11:15.210 --> 00:11:18.240
of the four quantum numbers.

00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:21.320
So energy, once I
specify n, l, m, and s,

00:11:21.320 --> 00:11:26.950
you can give me the
energy and away we go.

00:11:26.950 --> 00:11:29.910
And the thing is that
you need to realize

00:11:29.910 --> 00:11:34.750
that the energy levels are
actually a function of electron

00:11:34.750 --> 00:11:35.690
occupancy.

00:11:35.690 --> 00:11:37.440
So you can look
carefully, if you get down

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:39.700
into the d orbitals
and the f orbitals,

00:11:39.700 --> 00:11:43.130
as you add one more
electron moving one element

00:11:43.130 --> 00:11:44.750
to the right on
the periodic table,

00:11:44.750 --> 00:11:49.470
sometimes you see the
population not adding by one,

00:11:49.470 --> 00:11:52.020
because the addition
of an electron

00:11:52.020 --> 00:11:56.200
changes the relative energies
of the various orbitals.

00:11:56.200 --> 00:12:00.930
So let's remember that,
that energy is a function

00:12:00.930 --> 00:12:05.130
of electron occupancy.

00:12:05.130 --> 00:12:08.520
Energy is a function
of electron occupancy.

00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:10.720
And then the third part
of the Aufbau principle

00:12:10.720 --> 00:12:13.070
is called Hund's rule.

00:12:13.070 --> 00:12:14.440
Hund's rule.

00:12:14.440 --> 00:12:18.550
Now, Hund is German for dog, but
this isn't named after a dog.

00:12:18.550 --> 00:12:22.590
This is named after Friedrich
Hund, a professor of physics

00:12:22.590 --> 00:12:24.200
at Frankfurt.

00:12:24.200 --> 00:12:25.590
He taught for many years.

00:12:25.590 --> 00:12:30.080
He died at the
tender age of 101.

00:12:30.080 --> 00:12:34.430
And he spoke about degeneracy.

00:12:34.430 --> 00:12:40.660
Not societal degeneracy,
but degeneracy in an atom.

00:12:40.660 --> 00:12:42.570
And this degeneracy
is the condition

00:12:42.570 --> 00:12:45.910
where you have a plurality of
orbitals at the same energy

00:12:45.910 --> 00:12:46.800
level.

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:52.150
So, in orbitals of
equivalent energy,

00:12:52.150 --> 00:12:58.510
in orbitals of
equivalent energy,

00:12:58.510 --> 00:13:01.265
we strive for
unpaired electrons.

00:13:01.265 --> 00:13:02.140
This is filling, now.

00:13:02.140 --> 00:13:04.280
This is how to direct
the filling sequence.

00:13:04.280 --> 00:13:14.390
Strive for unpaired electrons.

00:13:14.390 --> 00:13:16.820
Let's say unpaired
electron spins.

00:13:16.820 --> 00:13:18.640
Let's make it a little clearer.

00:13:18.640 --> 00:13:21.420
Unpaired electron spins.

00:13:21.420 --> 00:13:24.230
So I'm going to
give you an example,

00:13:24.230 --> 00:13:25.460
work through an example.

00:13:25.460 --> 00:13:28.180
So, what have we got here?

00:13:28.180 --> 00:13:29.540
Here's carbon.

00:13:29.540 --> 00:13:32.720
And if you look at any
element on the periodic table,

00:13:32.720 --> 00:13:34.150
you'll see this green.

00:13:34.150 --> 00:13:36.670
And this is the
electronic configuration.

00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:39.620
This tells you what
the sequence looks

00:13:39.620 --> 00:13:44.230
like for that particular element
in the neutral form, et cetera,

00:13:44.230 --> 00:13:47.520
et cetera, subject to
many, many considerations.

00:13:47.520 --> 00:13:49.910
So let's look at carbon.

00:13:49.910 --> 00:13:59.350
So if we look at carbon, it
tells us 1 s2, 2 s2, 2 p2.

00:13:59.350 --> 00:14:01.400
So what's all this mean?

00:14:01.400 --> 00:14:03.150
Well, it's all written
in code for us.

00:14:03.150 --> 00:14:06.340
So the first number
here is the n number.

00:14:06.340 --> 00:14:08.650
So this means n equals 1.

00:14:08.650 --> 00:14:12.030
s is the spectrocopist's
notation,

00:14:12.030 --> 00:14:14.740
so this means that l equals 0.

00:14:14.740 --> 00:14:20.780
And then the 2 here means
2 electron occupancy.

00:14:20.780 --> 00:14:27.650
So the 1s orbital is filled
to the tune of two electrons.

00:14:27.650 --> 00:14:29.750
And the 2s orbital
has two electrons,

00:14:29.750 --> 00:14:32.620
