This is the p orbitals.

00:46:27.500 --> 00:46:29.960
They're dumbbell-shaped.

00:46:29.960 --> 00:46:31.400
With two lobes.

00:46:31.400 --> 00:46:33.210
And if you have a
single electron,

00:46:33.210 --> 00:46:34.520
it doesn't reside in one lobe.

00:46:34.520 --> 00:46:36.755
It can jump from one
side to the other.

00:46:36.755 --> 00:46:39.380
You might say, well, how does it
get from one lobe to the other

00:46:39.380 --> 00:46:43.875
when halfway between,
there's a nodal plane.

00:46:43.875 --> 00:46:46.900
It has zero probability.

00:46:46.900 --> 00:46:50.660
Well, it's behaving as a wave.

