00:48:36.140 --> 00:48:41.500
And now it's 1941, the
Nazis have invaded Denmark.

00:48:41.500 --> 00:48:45.530
And Bohr is essentially
waiting to get out

00:48:45.530 --> 00:48:52.560
of Denmark before the war
overtakes the rest of Europe.

00:48:52.560 --> 00:48:55.970
Meanwhile, Heisenberg is now
the head of the Nazi equivalent

00:48:55.970 --> 00:48:57.550
of the Manhattan Project.

00:48:57.550 --> 00:49:00.770
And he goes to Copenhagen
to visit his old mentor.

00:49:00.770 --> 00:49:01.942
That's a fact.

00:49:01.942 --> 00:49:02.650
They have dinner.

00:49:02.650 --> 00:49:03.800
That's a fact.

00:49:03.800 --> 00:49:04.730
They go for a walk.

00:49:04.730 --> 00:49:05.780
That's a fact.

00:49:05.780 --> 00:49:08.090
They never speak to each
other after that night.

00:49:08.090 --> 00:49:09.490
That's a fact.

00:49:09.490 --> 00:49:12.290
So the question is,
what went on that night.

00:49:12.290 --> 00:49:15.680
And that's what Michael Frayn
uses as the dramatic point

00:49:15.680 --> 00:49:16.720
